# SkyWeb Analytics Change Log

Detailed implementation notes for SkyWeb feature phases and the .NET transition lane.

## DN-9.1 — ECharts + D3 Chart Engine Foundation

- Added Apache ECharts and D3 to the root SkyWeb package dependencies for the .NET migration lane.
- Replaced `apps/web-dotnet/SkyWeb.Client/src/components/Sparkline.jsx` with an ECharts-backed single-series line chart while preserving the existing component API used by chart panels and dashboard cards.
- Replaced `apps/web-dotnet/SkyWeb.Client/src/components/MultiSeriesSparkline.jsx` with an ECharts-backed multi-series comparison chart while preserving the existing component API used by `ChartPanel.jsx`.
- Used D3 `extent` and `ticks` helpers to compute stable y-axis ranges and tick values before handing options to ECharts.
- Added ECharts tooltip and chart-container styling to the .NET-lane client stylesheet.
- Cleared the DN-8 nullable build warning in `SkyWebAlertsService.CreateAlertRuleAsync` by safely falling back to the generated alert key and throwing an explicit reload error if the created row cannot be read back.
- Preserved the legacy `apps/web` chart components as rollback baseline; DN-9.1 targets only `apps/web-dotnet/SkyWeb.Client`.

## DN-8 — Alerts and Signal Center in C#

- Moved alert-rule CRUD, event history, alert-notification reads, acknowledge/dismiss actions, and Signal Center queue updates into native ASP.NET Core/C#.
- Kept alert evaluation routes proxied to SkyServer because the worker/evaluator remains the source of truth for writing evaluation events and notifications.

## DN-7.1 — Saved Views/Dashboards Build Stabilization

- Fixed the initial C# dashboard service build blocker caused by local variable shadowing.
- Cleared a nullable saved-view handoff warning.

## DN-7 — Saved Views and Dashboards in C#

- Moved saved-view CRUD, dashboard CRUD, and dashboard item CRUD into native ASP.NET Core/C#.
- Preserved enrichment with macro view metadata, indicator details, stats, default dashboards, layout presets, and item positioning.

## DN-6 — SkyWeb Profile and Preferences in C#

- Moved profile, member preferences, and alert preferences into native ASP.NET Core/C#.
- Preserved existing permission checks, default preference insertion, validation, and JSONB storage.

## DN-5.2 — Indicator Series Regclass/NaN Fix

- Cast PostgreSQL `to_regclass(...)` results to text before C# materialization.
- Scrubbed PostgreSQL numeric `NaN` values into JSON-safe nulls for indicator series responses.

## DN-5.1 — Public Macro Series Stabilization

- Hardened native C# public macro reads for indicator series and macro dashboard chart cards.

## DN-5 — Authentication in C#

- Moved login, logout, change-password, `/me`, and permissions into native ASP.NET Core/C#.
- Preserved opaque bearer tokens, SHA-256 session token storage, sliding expiry, login events, audit events, and app-scoped permissions.

## DN-4 — Public Macro REST Endpoints in C#

- Moved public macro summary, views, columns, latest rows, view detail, indicators, indicator detail, and indicator series endpoints into native ASP.NET Core/C#.

## DN-3 — .NET Client Wiring + Proxy Bridge

- Wired `SkyWeb.Client` to `SkyWeb.Api` and added temporary proxy fallback to SkyServer.
- Moved the .NET-lane client to port 5175 for side-by-side testing with the legacy app.

## DN-0 to DN-2 — .NET Foundation

- Preserved the pre-.NET baseline.
- Added the parallel `apps/web-dotnet` structure.
- Added ASP.NET Core health, DB health, CORS, Swagger, PostgreSQL connection factory, and development setup docs.

## Phase 8 — Macro Alerts

- Built alert rules, evaluation history, scheduler visibility, triggered notification queue, global signal surfacing, alert preferences, dedicated Signal Center, and alert-rule UX polish.
